</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taiwan's first athletic delegation to China in four decades arrived in Beijing 
to attend the Asian Junior Gymnastics Championships. The 15 athletes, 
accompanied by 12 coaches and officials, will compete for three days starting 
Friday, according to Chan Te-chi of the Chinese Taipei Olympic Committee. The 
visit marks the first time that Taiwan will be represented at a mainland sports 
event since 1949, when the Nationalists retreated from mainland China after 
defeat by the Communists. 
</P>
