<P>
The Food and Drug Administration, warning of the danger of botulism food 
poisoning, ordered a halt to the manufacture of garlic-in-oil mixes that 
require refrigeration but lack proper protective agents. The agency also urged 
consumers to discard commercial and homemade garlic-in-oil mixes that contain 
little or no acidifying agents such as citric and phosphoric acid. Most garlic 
products contain these additives, as disclosed on their labels, the FDA said. 
</P>
