<HEADLINE>
<P>
BODY OF MISSING GIRL, 13, FOUND IN MARIN COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NOVATO, Calif. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The nude body of 13-year-old Jennifer Moore, who has been missing since 
Thursday, was discovered Monday evening at the side of a local highway, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
"It appears . . . that she was probably killed elsewhere . . ," police 
spokesman Scott Sibbald said. "She was in some garbage bags, partially in and 
partially out. Part of her face and head were still concealed in the bags." 
</P>
<P>
Some of her clothes were found nearby, the spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Sibbald declined to elaborate on the condition of the body. An autopsy was 
scheduled by the Marin County coroner's office. 
</P>
<P>
Sibbald said a motorist driving along Novato Boulevard, about half a mile west 
of the city limit, spotted debris alongside the road, stopped to check, found 
the body and contacted police. 
</P>
<P>
Sibbald indicated investigators have a lead on "a suspect or suspects," but 
declined further comment. 
</P>
<P>
The popular eighth-grade student was last seen near a local shopping center, 
where she had gone to get an ice cream cone, her mother said. 
</P>
<P>
More than 20,000 posters appealing for help in locating Jennifer were 
distributed over the weekend. 
</P>
<P>
Family friend Jan Shippey called Jennifer "the sweetest; just a good girl." 
</P>
<P>
Jennifer's disappearance was the latest in a series of cases involving missing 
Bay Area girls. Ilene Misheloff, 13, disappeared Jan. 30 on her way to an ice 
rink in Dublin; Michaela Garecht, 9, was abducted outside a Hayward market last 
November, and Amber Swartz-Garcia disappeared while playing in the front yard 
of her Pinole home last June. 
</P>
<P>
However, investigators have said there is no evidence that the cases are 
connected. 
</P>
