<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: DRIVER HELD IN DEATH OF WOMAN CROSSING STREET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A74-year-old woman died Monday after she was struck by a car while walking 
across a Panorama City street, Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
Irma Martinez of Gardena died at Holy Cross Medical Center in Mission Hills 
several hours after the 3 p.m. accident, Officer Timothy Sands said. 
</P>
<P>
The driver, 34-year-old Edwin John Preimesberger of Lancaster, was arrested on 
suspicion of vehicular manslaughter and was being held at the Los Angeles 
Police Department's Van Nuys Jail, Sands said. Police said a breath test showed 
that the man was legally drunk when the accident occurred. 
</P>
<P>
The woman was walking in a crosswalk on Van Nuys Boulevard at Chase Street when 
she was struck by the car, which had run a red light, police said. The car was 
traveling about 35 m.p.h., Sands said. 
