<HEADLINE>
<P>
CSUN TO SIGN CERRITOS' HUMPHREY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE HISERMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Eugene Humphrey, a 6-0 guard who helped Cerritos College to the state junior 
college basketball championship, said Monday that he will sign a letter of 
intent with Cal State Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
Humphrey averaged 12.5 points and four assists for Cerritos, which finished the 
season with a 31-4 record. He converted 51% of his field-goal attempts and made 
46% from three-point range. He shot 80% from the free-throw line and played 
both point-guard and off-guard positions. 
</P>
<P>
The CSUN baseball team has signed Tustin pitcher Monte Jones, a 6-1, 175-pound 
right-hander who leads Orange County in strikeouts with 77 in 45 innings 
pitched. 
</P>
<P>
The Northridge softball team has signed Simi Valley's Denise Swank, a third 
baseman who has been an all-Marmonte League selection three times and was last 
season's team MVP for the Pioneers. 
</P>
<P>
Signing with the women's basketball program is Haily Griffith, a 6-1 forward 
who led Eureka High to a 24-4 record last season. MIKE HISERMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
