<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Crude Oil Prices Surge: After hovering near Friday's close for most of the day, 
oil prices rallied in late afternoon trading, following strong gains in 
gasoline prices ahead of the summer driving season. West Texas Intermediate, 
the benchmark U.S. crude, closed up 53 cents at $21.22 a barrel for May 
delivery on the New York Mercantile Exchange. May gasoline contracts firmed 
2.06 cents to 72.08 cents a gallon on the New York Mercantile. May heating oil 
was up 0.85 of a cent to 53.76 cents a gallon. "There are worries of 
longer-term supply problems going into the summer driving season," said one 
trader. 
</P>
</TEXT>
