<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ducommun: The troubled Carson aerospace company lost $19.4 milion for all of 
1988, compared to a $19.1-million loss for 1987. The company said that sales 
from its continuing operations declined 6% to $59.8 million in 1988. The 
company blamed its loss on inventory writedowns and cost overruns in two of its 
aerospace units and a $3.1-million loss related to the disposal of its cable 
assembly business. The company also said it lost $9.8 million on sales of $13.7 
million in the fourth quarter of 1988, compared to a loss of $21.5 million on 
sales of $14.9 million in the fourth of 1987. 
</P>
