<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: 1 KILLED, 6 HURT BY WRONG-WAY DRIVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A woman was killed and six people were injured Monday when a man driving the 
wrong way along a Sepulveda street struck two cars at an intersection, Los 
Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
Charlotte Knowlden, 66, of Bakersfield -- a passenger in one of the cars -- 
died at Holy Cross Medical Center in Mission Hills. Her husband, James 
Knowlden, 69, was in critical condition at the hospital. 
</P>
<P>
Michael Mare Jr., 34, of Arleta, was arrested on suspicion of vehicular 
manslaughter after the accident at Plummer Street and Sepulveda Boulevard, 
police said. Mare was in serious condition at Northridge Hospital Medical 
Center. 
</P>
<P>
Two victims were treated at a hospital for minor injuries and released, and two 
were treated at the scene, officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
