<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
CALTRANS PROJECTS WILL AFFECT TRAFFIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Caltrans officials announced several projects Monday that will affect traffic 
in several areas of Orange County during the next few weeks. 
</P>
<P>
Field survey operations for the eventual widening of the Riverside Freeway, 
California 91, began Monday and will continue for about 3 months, officials 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Field survey work will occur in the freeway median between Gypsum Canyon Road 
and the Orange-Riverside county line from 9 a.m. to 3 p.m. Surveying began 
eastbound Monday, and will continue westbound Tuesday, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Similar work between Weir Canyon Road and Gypsum Canyon Road will occur during 
the same hours eastbound on Wednesday, and westbound on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Between Coal Canyon Road and the Orange-Riverside county line, the same type of 
activity is scheduled eastbound for Friday, at the same hours. 
</P>
<P>
The No. 1 and 2 lanes on the northbound Santa Ana Freeway, Interstate 5, will 
be closed half a mile south and half a mile north of the Jeffrey Road exit for 
restriping from 11 p.m. today until 5 a.m. Wednesday. the No. 2 and 3 lanes 
will be closed at the same location for the same activity from 11 p.m. 
Wednesday until 5 a.m. Thursday. However, the northbound Jeffrey Road on- and 
off-ramps will also be closed as well as the northbound Sand Canyon on-ramp. 
</P>
<P>
Also, Del Mar Street at Newport Boulevard will be closed in both directions 
from 7 a.m. to 5 p.m. Wednesday for the construction of a detour related to the 
extension of the Costa Mesa Freeway, California 55. 
</P>
</TEXT>
