<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: EVICTION ORDINANCE TARGETS DRUG DEALERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
People who deal drugs in rented apartments or houses can be evicted by their 
landlords under an emergency ordinance passed by the Gardena City Council. 
</P>
<P>
Following the lead of the Los Angeles County Board of Supervisors, which passed 
a similar ordinance last month, the council voted 4 to 0 in favor of the 
measure that permits landlords to evict tenants for selling drugs. 
</P>
<P>
A landlord would be required to seek eviction of such tenants after a request 
by the Police Department, the district attorney or the city attorney. Landlords 
failing to seek eviction of drug-dealing tenants within 60 days face fines of 
up to $5,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
