However, the article on lobbying members of Congress omitted much of what 
actually occurred that day. 
</P>
<P>
I was a member of the delegation from Los Angeles that had a scheduled and 
confirmed appointment with both Sens. Cranston and Wilson. Wilson did not show 
up for this meeting, but sent an aide to represent his position on the issues. 
Cranston not only met with the entire 200-plus members of the delegation, he 
stayed for half an hour to answer all questions. 
</P>
<P>
LYNDA PALEVSKY 
