<HEADLINE>
<P>
LINCOLN'S WILHITE TO PLAY BASKETBALL WITH THE TITANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Aaron Wilhite, a 6-foot-8, 230-pound forward from San Diego Lincoln High 
School, has signed a national letter of intent to play basketball at Cal State 
Fullerton and will deliver it to the school today, Lincoln Coach Ron Loneski 
said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
The letter is not valid under National Collegiate Athletic Assn. rules until it 
is delivered to the school and filed in the conference office. 
</P>
<P>
Wilhite averaged 24 points and 12 rebounds a game this season for Lincoln, 
which finished 27-2, losing to Morningside in the first round of the state 
playoffs. He also set a San Diego Section record for rebounds in a game with 39 
against Hoover. 
</P>
<P>
Loneski said Wilhite had visited San Diego State and Oregon State and decided 
on Fullerton in part because of the school's engineering department. 
</P>
