LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
BANDITS HURT, ROB MAN, 91, IN BREA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 91-year-old man suffered a broken nose and several bruises to his head when 
he and his daughter were robbed at gunpoint Monday night outside the Christ 
Lutheran Church in Brea. 
</P>
<P>
Louise Joseph, 59, of Fullerton and her father, Carl Johnson, were entering the 
church at 820 W. Imperial Blvd. at 9:08 p.m. when he was struck in the head 
with the butt of a pistol, said Larry Labrecht principal of Christ Lutheran Day 
School. Joseph, a kindergarten teacher at the school, which adjoins the church, 
was going there to catch up on some work. 
</P>
<P>
Labrecht said Joseph was about to open the door "when she heard a commotion 
behind her and turned to see her father falling after being hit with the gun." 
The two thieves demanded the keys to Joseph's blue 1987 Nissan Maxima and fled 
in the car. Police have not found the car or the robbers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
