<P>
WALESA MEETS WITH JARUZELSKI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WARSAW 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Solidarity leader Lech Walesa and Communist Party chief Wojciech Jaruzelski met 
today for the first time in more than seven years, a day after the trade union 
was legalized. 
</P>
<P>
"I feel satisfaction. We have come a very difficult and long way," Jaruzelski 
told reporters after the meeting. "Reconciliation is a process, not an act," he 
said, and he cited the broad agreement on political and economic reform reached 
between communist authorities and the opposition. 
</P>
<P>
"Today we only put another seal, in a way, on that accord," he said. 
</P>
<P>
Walesa left the meeting without talking to reporters. 
